## 1. Feature Overview

Users can upload documents into a base-scoped file library, then attach any subset of those files to individual AI chat messages. The backend fetches the stored files, extracts their text content according to MIME type, and injects it into the LLM prompt inside `<file_context>` tags before the prompt reaches the agent.

Two interaction paths exist:

| Path | Trigger | Scope |
|------|---------|-------|
| **Upload new file** | Paperclip button → OS file picker | Current session queue, cleared after send |
| **Select from library** | Files button → checkbox popover | Persists across messages until manually unchecked |

Both paths produce `fileTokens: string[]` that are sent with every AI stream request.

