## 4. Storage Layer

Files live in the MinIO **private bucket** under the `chat-file/` directory prefix.

```typescript
// apps/nestjs-backend/src/features/attachments/plugins/adapter.ts
static readonly getBucket = (type: UploadType) => {
  // ...
  case UploadType.ChatFile:  // value = 13
    return storageConfig().privateBucket;
};

static readonly getDir = (type: UploadType) => {
  // ...
  case UploadType.ChatFile:
    return 'chat-file';
};
```

Using the private bucket means:
- No public URLs are generated; all read access goes through the backend.
- The presign endpoint generates a short-lived PUT URL so the client can upload the binary directly to MinIO, bypassing the backend for the transfer itself.
- `downloadFile` in `ChatFileService` streams bytes server-side at extraction time only.

