## 6. Backend Module

### Module Wiring

```
AppModule
├── ChatFileModule          (apps/nestjs-backend/src/features/chat-file/chat-file.module.ts)
│   ├── imports:    StorageModule          (provides StorageAdapter via Symbol.for('ObjectStorage'))
│   ├── controller: ChatFileController
│   ├── provider:   ChatFileService
│   └── exports:    ChatFileService
│
└── AiModule                (apps/nestjs-backend/src/features/ai/ai.module.ts)
    ├── imports:    SettingModule, ChatFileModule
    ├── controller: AiController
    └── provider:   AiService              (injects ChatFileService)
```

### `ChatFileController`

```
@Controller('api/:baseId/chat-files')

GET    /           @Permissions('base|read')    → chatFileService.listFiles(baseId)
POST   /           @Permissions('base|read')    → chatFileService.saveFile(baseId, body)
                   body validated with ZodValidationPipe(saveChatFileRoSchema)
DELETE /:fileId    @Permissions('base|delete')  → chatFileService.deleteFile(baseId, fileId)
```

### `ChatFileService` — Public API

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `listFiles(baseId)` | Returns all non-deleted files for a base, newest first. `BigInt(size)` is coerced to `Number`. |
| `saveFile(baseId, dto)` | Validates MIME type and size, writes a DB row. Throws `CustomHttpException(VALIDATION_ERROR)` on failure. |
| `deleteFile(baseId, fileId)` | Soft-deletes the DB row first, then best-effort removes the object from MinIO. Storage errors are caught and logged. |
| `buildFileContext(tokens[])` | **Pre-agent entry point.** Delegates to `extractTextFromTokens`, returns the formatted text block or `null`. |
| `extractTextFromTokens(tokens[])` | Fetches DB records by token, calls `extractTextFromFile` per record, joins results with `\n\n`. Failures for individual files are caught and logged; extraction continues. |

### `ChatFileService` — Private Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `extractTextFromFile(bucket, path, mimetype, filename)` | Downloads the object from MinIO, converts stream to buffer, dispatches to parser by MIME type. |
| `streamToBuffer(stream)` | Drains a Node.js `Readable` into a `Buffer` using `on('data')` / `on('end')` / `on('error')`. |

### `AiService` — File-Related Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `injectFileContext(prompt, fileTokens)` | Private. Calls `chatFileService.buildFileContext`, wraps result in `<file_context>` tags, prepends to prompt. Returns the original prompt unchanged if tokens are empty or all extractions fail. |
| `generateStream(baseId, ro, response)` | Public. Resolves model instance → calls `injectFileContext` → runs agent → pipes stream to HTTP response. |

