## 9. File Selection & Context Injection Pipeline

### Token Merging (Frontend)

```typescript
// ChatPanel.tsx — handleSubmit
const persistedTokens = chatFiles
  .filter((f) => selectedFileIds.has(f.id))
  .map((f) => f.token);

const uploadingTokens = uploadingFiles
  .filter((f) => !f.uploading && !f.error && f.token)
  .map((f) => f.token as string);

// Dedup: a file uploaded this session then also selected from picker counts once
const fileTokens = [...new Set([...persistedTokens, ...uploadingTokens])];
```

### Pre-Agent Injection (Backend)

```typescript
// ai.service.ts
private async injectFileContext(
  prompt: string,
  fileTokens: string[] | undefined
): Promise<string> {
  if (!fileTokens?.length) return prompt;
  const context = await this.chatFileService.buildFileContext(fileTokens);
  if (!context) return prompt;
  return `<file_context>\n${context}\n</file_context>\n\n${prompt}`;
}
```

```typescript
// chat-file.service.ts
async buildFileContext(tokens: string[]): Promise<string | null> {
  const text = await this.extractTextFromTokens(tokens);
  return text || null;
}
```

### Resulting Prompt Shape (Multi-File Example)

```
<file_context>
--- File: report.pdf ---
[extracted text from PDF]

--- File: notes.txt ---
[raw UTF-8 content]
</file_context>

You are a helpful data assistant.

User: Summarise the key findings from the report.
Assistant:
```

