## 10. Access Control

Every HTTP request passes through `AuthGuard` and `PermissionGuard` (registered globally in `GlobalModule` via `APP_GUARD`).

| Endpoint | Required permission | Rationale |
|----------|--------------------|-----------
| `GET  /{baseId}/chat-files` | `base\|read` | Read-only; listing does not expose file contents |
| `POST /{baseId}/chat-files` | `base\|read` | Registering an already-uploaded object reference is a read-level action; binary upload occurred directly against MinIO via a presigned URL gated by the attachments module |
| `DELETE /{baseId}/chat-files/{fileId}` | `base\|delete` | Destructive; requires explicit delete permission |

**Base scoping** is enforced at the service layer. `findFirst({ where: { id: fileId, baseId } })` ensures a request with a valid `fileId` but an incorrect `baseId` returns `NotFoundException`. This avoids leaking the existence of files in other bases via timing or error-code differences.

**Storage access control**: the private bucket is not accessible without backend credentials. Even if a presigned PUT URL were intercepted, it allows only a single write operation. Reading file content requires going through `ChatFileService.extractTextFromFile`, which is only invoked by the authenticated AI stream endpoint.

