## 12. Error Handling

| Scenario | Client behaviour | Server behaviour |
|----------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Invalid MIME type on upload | Shows error message; upload never starts | `saveFile` throws `CustomHttpException(VALIDATION_ERROR)` |
| File exceeds 10 MB | Shows error message; upload never starts | `saveFile` throws `CustomHttpException(VALIDATION_ERROR)` |
| MinIO PUT fails | Chip shows `{ error: 'Upload failed' }` | No DB row is created; token is never saved |
| MinIO DELETE fails on soft-delete | Invisible to user | `logger.warn`; DB soft-delete already committed; object becomes orphaned |
| Text extraction fails for one file | — | File is skipped with `logger.warn`; remaining files are still extracted; partial context is injected |
| File not found / wrong base on delete | — | `NotFoundException`; no DB or storage operation runs |
| User stops generation mid-stream | `AbortController.abort()` → fetch rejects with `AbortError` | Stream cancelled at SDK level |
| Empty assistant message on abort | Removed from local `messages` array | — |

